                <h2>Introduction</h2>
                <p>    
                    Numeric data transformation from "Gauss-Kruger" projection meridian zones is defined 
                    from coordinates x and y in two dimensional space.
                    In "HTRS96/TM" ,cartographic space is defined from numerical  data of coordinates "E" and "N"
                    in two dimensional space.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Transformation between those two projections are carried out on the basis of average geographical
                    coordinates "φ" and "λ".
                </p>

                <p>
                    So, final transformation would look like this: y,x => λ,φ  => E,N
                </p>

                <p>
                    On Croatian teritory there are two coordinate view's in "Gauss Kruger" projection of meridian zones.
               </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Fifth coordinate system </p>
                            <p>Origin of coordinate axis in: x = 0, in equatorial level φ = 0(degrees) </p>
                            <p>y = 5 500 000  (equivalent of y = 0), in equatorial level λ = 15 (degrees)</p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>Sixth coordinate system</p>
                            <p>with x = 0, and in equatorial level φ = 0(degrees) </p>
                            <p>and y= 6 500 000 = y = 0, in equatroial level λ = 18 (degrees)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                
                <p> 
                    Defined width of zone would be: ± 1˚ 30' from greenwich meridian and  λ = 15 (degrees)
                    or  λ = 18 (degrees);
                </p>

                <p>
                    Coordinate system of "HTRS96/TM" cartographic teritory covers whole teritory of Republic of Croatia with axis origins:
                    N = 0 [m] , and in equatorial level  φ = 0 ˚
                    E = 500 000 = 0 [m], and in equatorial level λ = 16˚ 30' 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Defined width of zone would be ± 3˚, and from greenwich meridian λ = 16˚ 30' 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Precision of algorithm used in this software is 10 E-15.
                </p>

                <a href="~/Images/transformation.jpg"><img HEIGHT=240 WIDTH=160 src="~/Images/transformation.jpg" /></a>

